Question: when creating a th1D, can we also write what the underflow and overflow bins should be?

Short answer: Yes — but not in the constructor.
You set underflow/overflow after creating the TH1D, by manually filling or writing to those bins.

When you create a TH1D like:
TH1D* h = new TH1D("h", "title", nbins, xmin, xmax);
ROOT automatically creates nbins + 2 bins:
	•	bin = 0 → underflow
	•	bin = 1 ... nbins → normal bins
	•	bin = nbins + 1 → overflow

You cannot specify the values for underflow/overflow in the constructor — because 
ROOT expects those to come from .Fill() or by setting them manually.

✔️ How to explicitly set underflow and overflow
Use SetBinContent or AddBinContent:

Set the underflow bin:
h->SetBinContent(0, underflow_value);

Set normal bins:
h->SetBinContent(i, value);   // i = 1...nbins

Set the overflow bin
h->SetBinContent(nbins + 1, overflow_value);

✔️ If you want to fill them instead of setting values (INCREMENTS EXISTING CONTENT BY SOME AMOUNT)
h->AddBinContent(0, weight);           // underflow
h->AddBinContent(nbins + 1, weight);   // overflow

✔️ Checking bin indices safely
int n = h->GetNbinsX();
double uf = h->GetBinContent(0);
double of = h->GetBinContent(n+1);
